## 3. Screen-by-Screen Analysis

### 🏠 Dashboard (default view)

**Components rendered:**

#### ➤ [PerformanceMetricsSection](file:///Users/clustox_1/Documents/MasterGroup-RecommendationSystem/mastergroup-analytics-dashboard/src/screens/Wireframe/sections/PerformanceMetricsSection/PerformanceMetricsSection.tsx#13-159)
- **API:** `GET /api/v1/analytics/dashboard?time_filter=&category=&order_source=&delivered_only=`
- **Hook:** `useDashboardMetrics({ timeFilter, category, orderSource, deliveredOnly })`
- **Display:** 4 colorful KPI cards in a responsive 2×2 / 4-column grid
  | Card | Color | Metric |
  |------|-------|--------|
  | Total Revenue | Green | `Rs X.XM` formatted |
  | Total Orders | Blue | formatted number |
  | Total Customers | Orange | formatted number |
  | Avg Order Value | Purple | `Rs X,XXX` |
- Status dot: 🟢 Engine Online / 🔴 Engine Offline (health check)

#### ➤ `TopProductsSection`
- **API:** `GET /api/v1/recommendations/popular?limit=10&time_filter=&category=`
- **Display:** Ranked list / table of top products with purchase counts, revenue, unique customers
- Supports category filter + order source filter

#### ➤ `POSvsOESection`
- **API:** Likely calls dashboard with OE/POS breakdown
- **Display:** OE vs POS comparison charts, revenue split, order count comparison

#### ➤ `OrderStatusAnalyticsSection`
- **API:** `GET /api/v1/analytics/order-status-breakdown?time_filter=&order_source=`
- **Display:** OE statuses (Delivered/Cancelled/Returned/Pending/...) + POS (completed)
  - Fulfillment rate, lost revenue metric
  - Separate OE and POS breakdowns

#### ➤ `RecentActivitySection`
- **API:** Likely `/analytics/recent-orders` or similar
- **Display:** Recent order feed / activity log

---

### 👥 Customer Profiling
**Component:** `CustomerDetailedProfiling`  
**API calls:**
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/customers/rfm-segments` — segment summary
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/customer-similarity?time_filter=&category=` — similar customer pairs
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/customers/at-risk` — customers going dormant

**Display:**
- Customer cards with purchase history
- Segment badges (Champions, At Risk, etc.)
- Similarity score display
- Customer search / drilldown

---

### 💡 Cross-Selling / Revenue Optimization
**Component:** `CrossSellingSection`  
**API calls:**
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/collaborative-pairs?time_filter=&order_source=&category=` — product pairs
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/collaborative-products` — frequently bought items

**Display:**
- Product pair cards (Product A + Product B bought together)
- Co-purchase count, combined revenue
- Filterable by OE vs POS source

---

### 🤝 Collaborative Filtering (`CollaborativeRecommendationDashboard`)
**API calls:**
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/collaborative-metrics` — overall CF metrics (falls back to mock if endpoint missing)
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/collaborative-products` — top products identified by CF
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/customer-similarity` — customer-to-customer similarity data

**Display:**
- Metric cards: Total Recommendations, Avg Similarity Score, Active Customer Pairs, Algorithm Accuracy
- Top collaborative products table: recommendation_count, avg_similarity_score, total_revenue
- Customer similarity list: top similar customer pairs + shared products

---

### 🗺️ Geographic Intelligence
**Component:** [GeographicIntelligenceSection](file:///Users/clustox_1/Documents/MasterGroup-RecommendationSystem/mastergroup-analytics-dashboard/src/screens/Wireframe/sections/GeographicIntelligenceSection/GeographicIntelligenceSection.tsx#16-214)  
**API calls (parallel):**
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/geographic/provinces?time_filter=&order_source=&category=`
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/geographic/cities?time_filter=&limit=10&order_source=&category=`

**Display:**
1. **Province Performance List** — each province shows:
   - Region badge (North/South/Central/East/West colored)
   - Province name + `X orders · Y customers`
   - Revenue in PKR  
   - **Blue gradient progress bar** showing market share % vs max province
2. **Top Cities Table** — ranked table with:
   - `#1 #2 #3` highlighted badges
   - City name, Province badge (region-colored), Orders, Revenue, Customers

**ExplanationCard** embedded: methodology explanation (61-city mapping database, province aggregation logic)

> Insight hardcoded in ExplanationCard: "Punjab leads with 86K+ orders and PKR 4.8B revenue (93% of total)" — this text may need updating as data grows.

---

### 📊 RFM Customer Segmentation
**Component:** [RFMSegmentationSection](file:///Users/clustox_1/Documents/MasterGroup-RecommendationSystem/mastergroup-analytics-dashboard/src/screens/Wireframe/sections/RFMSegmentationSection/RFMSegmentationSection.tsx#15-408)  
**API calls:**
- `GET /api/v1/ml/rfm-segments?time_filter=` — ML-powered RFM (primary, no SQL fallback)
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/customers/segment-details/{segment}?limit=20` — on segment click

**9 Customer Segments with emoji + color + priority:**
| Segment | Icon | Color | Action |
|---------|------|-------|--------|
| Champions | 🏆 | Yellow | VIP Treatment |
| Loyal Customers | ⭐ | Green | Maintain |
| Potential Loyalists | 🎯 | Blue | Convert |
| New Customers | 🌱 | Cyan | Onboard |
| At Risk | ⚠️ | Orange | Win Back |
| Cannot Lose Them | 🚨 | Red | URGENT |
| Need Attention | 💬 | Purple | Re-engage |
| Hibernating | 💤 | Gray | Reactivate |
| Lost | 📉 | Slate | Low Priority |

**Display (4 parts):**
1. **Bar Chart** — clickable bars showing customer count per segment proportionally (height = % of max)
2. **3-column Card Grid** — each segment card shows: customer_count, %, total_revenue, avg_order_value, avg_orders, days since last order
3. **Drill-down Table** (on segment click) — top 20 customers with Name/City/Orders/Spent/Last Order/R-F-M badges
4. **Recommended Actions** — 3 strategy cards: VIP Program (Champions count), Win-Back (At Risk count), Reactivation (Hibernating count)

---

### 🤖 ML Recommendations (`AWSPersonalizeSection`)
**API calls:**
- `GET /api/v1/ml/status` — model training status, which of 4 algorithms are trained
- `POST /api/v1/ml/train` — trigger manual training from UI
- `GET /api/v1/ml/recommendations/{userId}` — per-user recommendations
- `GET /api/v1/ml/top-products` — ML-identified top products
- `GET /api/v1/ml/product-pairs` — ML-identified product pairs
- `GET /api/v1/ml/customer-similarity` — ML customer similarity

**Display (`MLStatusDashboard` component):**
- Model status: is_trained, training_timestamp, which of 4 algorithms are active
- `🤖 ML-Powered` or `📊 SQL-Based` badge on each section
- Manual training trigger button (admin)
- Recommendation display per user ID input

